\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces $L_F$ estimator 95\% bootstrap CIs and resulting $K^\star $. LCLS gives a tight CI ($\hat  L_F \approx 3$ Mendelian, $\approx 4.5$ Complex) and a realisable $K^\star $ (22 / 50). Isotonic envelope is loose. Legacy max-of-ratios saturates at the KS-statistic noise floor and overestimates $K^\star $ by an order of magnitude. The modal nested-CV $\hat  K(c_{\mathrm  {outer}}) \in \{5, 8\}$ (Mendelian) and $5$ (Complex) is the binding finite-sample constraint, well below all three asymptotic $K^\star $ predictions.}}{25}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:lf_forest}{{2}{25}{$L_F$ estimator 95\% bootstrap CIs and resulting $K^\star $. LCLS gives a tight CI ($\hat L_F \approx 3$ Mendelian, $\approx 4.5$ Complex) and a realisable $K^\star $ (22 / 50). Isotonic envelope is loose. Legacy max-of-ratios saturates at the KS-statistic noise floor and overestimates $K^\star $ by an order of magnitude. The modal nested-CV $\hat K(c_{\mathrm {outer}}) \in \{5, 8\}$ (Mendelian) and $5$ (Complex) is the binding finite-sample constraint, well below all three asymptotic $K^\star $ predictions}{figure.2}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Bootstrap distribution of HCCP $\hat  {\sigma }$-bin gap across $B = 200$ chromosome-level resamples. Mendelian (left) shows substantial right-skew driven by replicates that include high-gap chromosomes (chr6 / chr19 / chr20, see Tab.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:perchrom}); the all-chrom point estimate $0.077$ sits on the right tail of the distribution, while the bootstrap mean $0.020$ is closer to the centre. Complex (right) is much tighter (point and bootstrap mean both $\approx 0.02$).}}{25}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:bootstrap_density}{{3}{25}{Bootstrap distribution of HCCP $\shat $-bin gap across $B = 200$ chromosome-level resamples. Mendelian (left) shows substantial right-skew driven by replicates that include high-gap chromosomes (chr6 / chr19 / chr20, see Tab.~\ref {tab:perchrom}); the all-chrom point estimate $0.077$ sits on the right tail of the distribution, while the bootstrap mean $0.020$ is closer to the centre. Complex (right) is much tighter (point and bootstrap mean both $\approx 0.02$)}{figure.3}{}}
