\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {21}{\ignorespaces Worst-cell coverage gap $G(\hat  K_{\mathrm  {CV}})$ (mean $\pm $ SE over 5 replicates) on synthetic data, $L_F = 4$. The dimension-free claim of T5.1 is visible as approximately matching values across $d$ at fixed $(n, \pi _{\qopname  \relax m{min}})$; the $\pi _{\qopname  \relax m{min}}^{-1/2}$ constant is visible as the $\pi _{\qopname  \relax m{min}} = 0.50$ rows being roughly $\sqrt  {5} \approx 2.24\times $ smaller than $\pi _{\qopname  \relax m{min}} = 0.10$ at matched $n$.}}{31}{table.21}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:synthetic_t5}{{21}{31}{Worst-cell coverage gap $G(\hat K_{\mathrm {CV}})$ (mean $\pm $ SE over 5 replicates) on synthetic data, $L_F = 4$. The dimension-free claim of T5.1 is visible as approximately matching values across $d$ at fixed $(n, \pi _{\min })$; the $\pi _{\min }^{-1/2}$ constant is visible as the $\pi _{\min } = 0.50$ rows being roughly $\sqrt {5} \approx 2.24\times $ smaller than $\pi _{\min } = 0.10$ at matched $n$}{table.21}{}}
